headline: SoFi Stock Didn’t Get Enough of a ‘Trump Bump.’ How Other Payment Companies Fared.
summary: The market did a tap dance Wednesday following news that Donald Trump had won the presidency, and payment stocks certainly were celebrating.  To better understand why, Mizuho Securities analyst Dan Dolev sorted them into a trio of move categories: those whose moves were deserved, stocks that didn’t rise enough, and shares that have gone too far.  Robinhood  gained 20% to $29.86 on Wednesday, and though the recent flurry of trading activity likely isn’t sustainable, Mizuho believes the crypto company’s mix of financial services should benefit from an uptick in user engagement.
